cubes.name: deployments
cubes.title: Corn Deployments
cubes.description: The depolyment view provides key information across various key metrics like Density, By Location, H2H Agronomics,  H2H Artificial Greensnap, H2H Disease, H2H Maturity, H2H Yield for a given head product. It helps users to view the performance pf heads against checks. Bio Economic Index (BEI) - Demonstrates strength of product fit for yield/moisture and agronomic traits by product segment.                 By Location - Provides more information related to Yield Performance, Agronomic, and Stress.  Uses current year by location data to show the trend of entry compared with check mean against the set mean and for performance the average win-rate across locations versus check mean. Density -  Is based on an integrated-density-testing (IDT) scheme that uses the standard GXE set as the mid density and, relative to it at a location level, includes a high density set (+5K PPA) and a low density set (-5K PPA).  The high and low sets are paired with standard GXE at 20 locations in core RMs, and 14 locations in other RMs (5 for RM70-80).   For the year - 2024, each set only contains 2 to 3 checks.  BLUP analysis predicts relative density response interaction and overall hybrid performance by density. H2H Agronomics - It shares performance information about the key characteristics like Test Weight, Root Lodging, Stalk Lodging, Plant Height, Ear Height, CCRVIG H2H Artificial Greensnap - Measures potential for greensnap based on artificial induction. H2H Maturity - It shares key information about Moisture,  S50, P50 etc.. H2H Disease - It shares key information of head product against check for different disease rating point like GLS, NCLB, Goss' Wilt, ASR, Tar Spot, Southern Rust etc H2H Yield – Performance of head against selected checks or all of the checks. Product - It's all the head product  and its precommcial product names

cubes.name: edited_allele_analysis
cubes.title: Edited Allele Analysis
cubes.description: A combined view of EditedAlleleCallID, EditedAlleleID, and SMEv2SEQProject_meta_data to provide a unified dataset for allele analysis and sequencing project metadata.

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.count_distinct_edited_allele_call_id
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Distinct Count of Edited Allele Call ID
measures.description: This is to get Distinct count of Edited Allele Call ID
measures.shortTitle: Distinct Count of Edited Allele Call ID

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.sum_of_allele_call_read_count
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Total Allele Call Reads
measures.description: This is to get sum of Allele Call Read Counts

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.count_distinct_seqlims_project
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Distinct Count of Sequence Project
measures.description: This is to get distinct count of Sequence Project

measures.name: edited_allele_analysis.count_distinct_edited_allele_id
measures.title: Edited Allele Analysis Distinct Count of Edited Allele ID
measures.description: This is to get Distinct count of Edited Allele ID
measures.shortTitle: Distinct Count of Edited Allele ID

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.edited_allele_call_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Edited Allele Call ID
dimensions.description: A concatenation of Sample ID Product 360 (p360) curated reference assembly including the chromosome or contig pollux ID identifying the guide used coordinate of the guide on the reference assembly and local_CIGAR. This makes this effectively a UUID for SME2.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.sample_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sample ID
dimensions.description: The Sample ID as designated by the LIMS system note is a concatenation of underscore separated SEQID and sample number.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.call_ref_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reference ID
dimensions.description: The Bayer Product 360 curated reference assembly including the chromosome (contig) the allele is on.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.barcode
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Barcode
dimensions.description: Barcode refers to the plant barcode or gds barcode as provided from LIMS and importantly is sample specific.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.reagent
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reagent
dimensions.description: This generally refers to constructs or pMONs but in the future could indicate other methodologies for introducing foreign DNA.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.guide_name
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Guide Name
dimensions.description: Pollux ID from SeqUR for the guide used to create this edit.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_call_read_count
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Call Read Counts
dimensions.description: Count of reads with this allele call covering the guide window.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.percent_of_reads_covering_guide
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Percent Reads
dimensions.description: Percentage of reads covering the guide with this exact allele. Calculated as allele_call_read_count over total_reads_covering_guide.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.hamming_distance
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Hamming Distance
dimensions.description: Number of differences between two sequences of the same length in this case the reference sequence and aligned read sequence.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_call_date_time
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Call Uploaded Datetime
dimensions.description: A timestamp of when this record was uploaded for discriminating between updates - usually due to reruns.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.seqlims_project
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Project
dimensions.description: SEQID is the discrete unit of projects that go through the sequencing lab and groups a set of samples that were sequenced together in a library.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.sequencing_run
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Run ID
dimensions.description: The run identifier from the sequencer that this project was ran on for backtracking and unifying with sequencing QC.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.number_of_samples_included
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Samples Included
dimensions.description: The number of samples that were above the minimum required threshold (and met QC criteria) for inclusion in analysis.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.number_of_samples_excluded
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Samples Excluded
dimensions.description: The number of samples that were not above the minimum required threshold (or did not meet other QC criteria) for inclusion in analysis.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.analysis_cutoff_used
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Analysis Cutoff Used
dimensions.description: A float used to cutoff the analysis and keep noise due to sequencing error out of the results.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.min_reads_used
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Min Reads Used
dimensions.description: The minimum number of reads that must be present for a sample to be retained in the results otherwise filtered out.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.sequencing_project_date_time
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Project Uploaded Datetime
dimensions.description: A timestamp of when this record was uploaded for discriminating between updates - usually due to reruns.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.edited_allele_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Edited Allele ID
dimensions.description: A concatenation of reference name identifier with chromosome (contig) 5' coordinate start of guide and local CIGAR.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_type
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Type
dimensions.description: Type of allele, one of 'edit', 'wt', or 'offsite'.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.edited_allele_ref_id
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reference ID
dimensions.description: The Bayer Product 360 curated reference assembly including the chromosome (contig) the allele is on.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.fp_sequence
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Five Prime Sequence
dimensions.description: Five prime sequence which is the sequence upstream of the guide window not including gaps.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.tp_sequence
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Three Prime Sequence
dimensions.description: Three prime sequence which is the sequence downstream of the guide window not including gaps.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.ref_string
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Reference string
dimensions.description: The wild-type or reference sequence of the guide region.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.match_string
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Sequence Match string
dimensions.description: The sequence of the read aligned segment for the allele.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.CIGAR
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis CIGAR(Compact Idiosyncratic Gapped Alignment Report)
dimensions.description: Compact idiosyncratic gapped alignment report for the entire read with respect to the edited allele.

dimensions.name: edited_allele_analysis.allele_date_time
dimensions.title: Edited Allele Analysis Allele Uploaded Datetime
dimensions.description: A timestamp of when this record was uploaded for discriminating between updates - usually due to reruns.

cubes.name: location360
cubes.title: Weather(TWC)
cubes.description: The Weather Company (TWC) historical weather data provides a global coverage for Bayer area of interest from 1979 to present. Location360 is collaborating with The Climate Corporation (TCC) on building this historical weather data archive.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest temperature recorded during the day. Also called min temp, daily low temp, lowest temperature.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest temperature recorded during the day. Also called max temp, daily high temp, peak temperature.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_midpoint_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Midpoint Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the midpoint between daily max and min temperatures. Also called mid temp, temperature midpoint, average extreme temp.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average temperature. Also called mean temp, daily mean temperature, average temperature.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_dew_point_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Dew Point Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest dew point temperature recorded during the day. Also called max dew point, peak dew point, daily high dew point.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Maximum Dew Point Temperature

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_dew_point_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Dew Point Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest dew point temperature recorded during the day. Also called min dew point, daily low dew point, lowest dew point.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Minimum Dew Point Temperature

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_dew_point_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Dew Point Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average dew point temperature. Also called mean dew point, average dew point, daily mean dew point.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Average Dew Point Temperature

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_wind_speed
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Wind Speed
measures.description: It is the average value of the maximum wind speed recorded during the day. Also called max wind, peak wind speed, daily high wind.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_wind_speed
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Wind Speed
measures.description: It is the average value of the minimum wind speed recorded during the day. Also called min wind, daily low wind, lowest wind speed.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_wind_speed
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Wind Speed
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average wind speed. Also called mean wind, average wind speed, daily mean wind.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_wind_speed_2m
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Wind Speed at 2m
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average wind speed measured at 2 meters above ground. Also called avg wind 2m, wind speed 2m avg, mean wind 2m.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Average Wind Speed at 2m

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_wind_speed_2m
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Wind Speed at 2m
measures.description: It is the average value of the minimum wind speed at 2 meters above ground. Also called min wind 2m, lowest wind 2m, wind speed 2m min.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Minimum Wind Speed at 2m

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_wind_speed_2m
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Wind Speed at 2m
measures.description: It is the average value of the maximum wind speed at 2 meters above ground. Also called max wind 2m, peak wind 2m, wind speed 2m max.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Maximum Wind Speed at 2m

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_wind_gust
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Wind Gust
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest wind gust recorded during the day. Also called max gust, peak wind gust, daily high gust.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_wind_direction
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Wind Direction
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average wind direction over the day (in degrees). Also called mean wind direction, wind dir avg, average wind bearing.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_relative_humidity
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Relative Humidity
measures.description: It is the average value of the maximum relative humidity recorded during the day. Also called max rh, peak humidity, daily high humidity, maximum relative humidity.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_relative_humidity
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Relative Humidity
measures.description: It is the average value of the minimum relative humidity recorded during the day. Also called min rh, daily low humidity, lowest humidity, minimum relative humidity.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_relative_humidity
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Relative Humidity
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average relative humidity. Also called mean rh, average humidity, daily mean relative humidity.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_atmospheric_pressure
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Atmospheric Pressure
measures.description: It is the average value of the highest atmospheric pressure recorded during the day. Also called max pressure, peak pressure, daily high pressure.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_min_atmospheric_pressure
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Minimum Atmospheric Pressure
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest atmospheric pressure recorded during the day. Also called min pressure, daily low pressure, lowest pressure.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_avg_atmospheric_pressure
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Average Atmospheric Pressure
measures.description: It is the average value of the daily average atmospheric pressure. Also called mean pressure, average pressure, daily mean pressure.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_total_precipitation
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Total Precipitation
measures.description: It is the average value of the total precipitation (rainfall/snowfall) during the day. Also called precip total, daily rainfall, total rain, precipitation.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_max_downward_solar_radiation
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Maximum Downward Solar Radiation
measures.description: It is the average value of the maximum solar radiation received at the surface. Also called max solar radiation, peak solar flux, daily high solar radiation.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Maximum Downward Solar Radiation

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_total_downward_solar_radiation
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Total Downward Solar Radiation
measures.description: It is the average value of the total solar radiation received during the day. Also called total solar radiation, solar flux total, daily solar energy.
measures.shortTitle: Average Daily Total Downward Solar Radiation

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_eto
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Evapotranspiration (ETO)
measures.description: It is the average value of the reference evapotranspiration (ETo) for the day. Also called eto, evapotranspiration reference, daily eto value.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_etr
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Evapotranspiration (ETR)
measures.description: It is the average value of the radiation-based evapotranspiration (ETr) for the day. Also called etr, evapotranspiration radiation, daily etr value.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_daily_day_length
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Daily Day Length
measures.description: It is the average value of the duration of daylight hours for the day. Also called daylight hours, sunlight duration, daily sun hours.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_min_temperature
measures.title: Weather(TWC) Average Minimum Temperature
measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest temperature recorded during the day. Also called Min Temp, Daily Low Temp, Lowest Temperature.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_max_temperature

measures.name: location360.avg_of_min_dew_point_temperature

measures.description: It is the average value of the lowest dew point temperature recorded during the day. Also called Min Dew Point Temp.

measures.name: location360.avg_of_max_dew_point_temperature

measures.name: location360.avg_of_avg_wind_speed

measures.name: location360.avg_of_min_relative_humidity

measures.name: location360.avg_of_max_relative_humidity

cubes.name: seed_processing
cubes.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing
cubes.description: Seed processing is the first step in the process of preparing seeds for planting post harvest.  The main goal is to enhance seed quality while also gathering quantity and sizing data.  This process can include shelling, cleaning, sorting, sizing, counting and treating seed. The current source for seed information is Shellmatic. Shellmatic is  IT system that enables overall Seed Processing system

dimensions.name: seed_processing.src_plot_bid
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Plot Barcode
dimensions.description: It is formatted as a string starting with 'P' followed by 23 integers. An example is 'P00000000879548099137769'. It is generated in Enterprise data systems from SPI (seed processing instruction) API.  It is a barcode applied to the plot corresponding to when the genetic material was produced. It is called as Source Plot Bid or Source Plot Barcode

dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Treatment Name
dimensions.description: Is a unique value string of variable length alphabets and special characters, with an upper limit of 255 characters.  It is generated from legacy excel file created by Gregg Pope. It represents the name of treatment applied to the batch.  It is displayed as 'CL/MX for US/LAN (Poncho)'.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treater_pump_volume
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Treatment Pump Volume
dimensions.description: Is a float value that represents the amount of treatment applied to the batch in mL.  It is generated from the shellmatic 3 PC application. It is displayed as '21.9384' It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treater_dry_time
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Treatment Dry Time
dimensions.description: Is a variable length field storing an integer value. It represents the amount of time in seconds the batch is allowed to dry. It is displayed as '80'. It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treater_pump_speed
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Treatment Pump Seed
dimensions.description: Is a floating point value that represents the RPM setting of the treater pump used for the batch.  It is generated from the settings file of the application. It is displayed as '150'.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treater_pump_vol_per_rev
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Volume Per Revolution
dimensions.description: Is a float value that represents the amount of treatment delivered with each revolution of the pump in mL.  Treater pump volume per revolution is generated from the settings file of the shelmatic and can be calibrated by the application. It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treater_treatment_rate

dimensions.description: Is a float value that represents the amount of treatment to be applied per 1000 seeds.  It is generated from legacy excel file created by Gregg Pope. It is displayed as '0.0. It is a seed treater. It is part of seed treament process.

In the mactracker_nsp table, if the barcode starts with P, source is Midas. If the barcode is fully numeric, source is velocity.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.batch_num_of_packets
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Packets in Batch
dimensions.description: It is the number of packets in the source batch. It is an instruction or parameter given to the process. It takes values from 1-5 and is fixed for the batch, if the batch is getting split into 3, all the packets will have the same value.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.input_barcode
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Input Barcode
dimensions.description: It is an alphanumeric unique combination of 24 characters generated in ascending order. It is a barocde applied to the packets corresponding to when the genetic material is distributed into packets from the source batch. It is displayed as 'P00000000879560012886300'. In the mactracker_nsp table, if the barcode starts with P, source is Midas. If the barcode is fully numeric, source is velocity.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.color_sorter_recipe
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Color Sorter Recipe
dimensions.description: Is an alphanumeric, free text field representing color sorter recipe.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.season
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Season
dimensions.description: Is the season of the field. It is the season the field was planted. Format: yyyy:mm, Year:month. Example: 2021:04

dimensions.name: seed_processing.data_source
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Data Source
dimensions.description: Almost always 'MIDAS' maybe someday we'll have VELOCITY Sources.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.scw
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Seed Cotton Weight(SCW)
dimensions.description: This is the Seed Cotton Weight observation for the cotton boll sample.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.scw_uom
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing SCW UOM
dimensions.description: Is the Seed Cotton Weight Unit of measure, used as Grams.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.lint
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Lint
dimensions.description: This is the Lint Weight observation when delinted.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.lint_uom
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Lint UOM
dimensions.description: This is the Lint Weight Unit of measure, used as Grams.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.fsw
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Fuzzy Seed Weight(FSW)
dimensions.description: This the Fuzzy Seed Weight observation when delinted.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.fsw_uom
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing FSW UOM
dimensions.description: This is the Fuzzy Seed Weight Unit of measure, used as Grams.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.lp
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Lint Percent
dimensions.description: Is the Lint Percent of the cotton sample. Calculated as follows: LINT/(LINT+FSW)

dimensions.name: seed_processing.turn_out
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Turn Out
dimensions.description: This is the Lint/SCW percent

dimensions.name: seed_processing.gin
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing GIN
dimensions.description: This is the computer name used during cotton processing in Ginning Support Program(GSP) Desktop app.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.bsw
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Black Seed Weight
dimensions.description: This is the Black Seed Weight observation.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.bsw_uom
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing BSW UOM
dimensions.description: Black Seed Weight Unit of measure, used as Grams.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.box
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Box ID
dimensions.description: This is the Box ID label used to group the cotton samples for the HVI system.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.bolp
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Bolls Per Plant(BOLP)
dimensions.description: Bolls per plant observation.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.gin_date
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Gin Date
dimensions.description: This is the date and time the sample was last processed.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.set_setId
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Velocity Set ID
dimensions.description: A Set ID refers to the unique identifier for a planned planting or grow-out of material in a field or controlled environment.  Each set can consist of sub-units called entries, which may contain different materials.  The Set ID is essential for tracking and managing these plantings effectively

dimensions.name: seed_processing.set_entryId
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Velocity Entry ID
dimensions.description: This is a system generated unique identifier created upon creation of an entry in the Velocity application.  Entry ID is same as Entity ID. It is also called as plot_id or plot id in the FTS application

dimensions.name: seed_processing.protocol_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Protocol ID
dimensions.description: It is a system generated unique identifier for this protocol. Protocol is a central location where all of your plans and operational instructions are linked together, serving as a starting point for your workflow in Velocity.  It consists of a collection of templates from various applications that can be copied as needed to carry out different workflows.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.protocol_name
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Protocol Name
dimensions.description: It is the name of the protocol

dimensions.name: seed_processing.germplasm_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: A Germplasm ID is a unique identifier assigned to a specific germplasm, which is a collection of genetic resources for an organism.  This ID helps in tracking and managing genetic materials, ensuring that each germplasm can be accurately referenced in databases and inventories.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.velmat_material_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Velocity Material ID
dimensions.description: A Material ID in Velocity is a globally unique identifier for a Velocity material. This could refer to an inventory barcode, lot ID,  or catalog item ID, depending on whether it pertains to an inventory, lot, or catalog item.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.access_growergroups
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Access Grower Groups
dimensions.description: This provides the information about the growers groups associated to the record

dimensions.name: seed_processing.access_usergroups
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Access user Groups
dimensions.description: User Groups are defined by business and consist of users from similar roles, squads, or units.  They enable visibility, sharing, and editing of trials among squad and unit members, facilitating collaboration and accountability

dimensions.name: seed_processing.relative_maturity
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing RM
dimensions.description: Relative Maturity (RM) is a measurement in agronomy that assists farmers in determining which hybrids to use for their crops with the RM often tied to yield.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.sets_material_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Inventory ID
dimensions.description: An inventory ID is typically a unique identifier assigned to a specific inventory item within a system like MIDAS. It helps in tracking and managing inventory accurately.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.population_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Population ID
dimensions.description: a Population ID refers to a unique identifier assigned to a specific Population. This ID helps in managing and tracking the associated data of that Population

dimensions.name: seed_processing.set_name
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Set Name
dimensions.description: A set name refers to the title given to a planned planting or grow out of material in a field or controlled environment.  Each set can be composed of sub-units called entries (such as plots, plants, or pots), and the set name helps to identify and manage these groupings effectively.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.line_type
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Line Type
dimensions.description: It is legacy piece of data that can be HYBRID, FINISHED, CODED, or SEGPOP.  This typically refers to the specific genetic lines being used in the breeding process. Different line types may have distinct genetic backgrounds and traits.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.line_code
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Line Code
dimensions.description: It is an user defined name applied to a given germplasm

dimensions.name: seed_processing.pedigree
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Pedigree
dimensions.description: Pedigree refers to a concatenated value that includes components such as Origin, Lineage or Line Code, and Precommercial name. It is string version of parental ancestry

dimensions.name: seed_processing.origin
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Origin
dimensions.description: The Origin in the Line Advancement Plan set entries refers to the specific source or lineage of materials, which are essential for tracking material development.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.genetic_material_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Genetic Material ID
dimensions.description: This captures midas genetic material id

dimensions.name: seed_processing.fts_germplasmid
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing FTS Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: The Germplasm resource identifier from FTS application

dimensions.name: seed_processing.sets_material_name
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Set Material Name
dimensions.description: It is material name of the set. a material name typically refers to the name associated with a specific material that used in the set. This could be linked to the Material ID, which is a globally unique identifier for a Velocity material, such as an inventory barcode, lot ID, or catalog item ID.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.catalog_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Catalog ID
dimensions.description: A Catalog ID is a unique identifier generated by the Velocity system for a specific catalog record.  It is used to describe a unique material and the attributes associated with that material, helping to tie together all the lots and inventories that represent the same material

dimensions.name: seed_processing.catalog_seed_type
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Catalog Seed Type
dimensions.description: The seed type of the catalog. For example Internal Seed, Commercial Check

dimensions.name: seed_processing.p360_product_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing p360 Product ID
dimensions.description: Describes the product 360 product identifier for velocity experiments. If the plants in the experiment are associated to a product intended to sell, this field will have values

dimensions.name: seed_processing.source_str
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Source String
dimensions.description: The Test Set name corresponding to when the genetic material was produced.source_str from midas for a genetic material, business logic stored in text box based on linecode of parents

dimensions.name: seed_processing.is_transgenic
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Is Trangenic
dimensions.description: Flag indicating if the germplasm contains a transgenic event

dimensions.name: seed_processing.transgenic_events
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Transgenic Events
dimensions.description: List of transgenic events Transgenic Events represent foreign DNA from usually the same species inserted purposefully into a new speciemen through a vector

dimensions.name: seed_processing.constructs
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Constructs
dimensions.description: This field contains the identities of the constructs used in the transformation process, provided the germplasm contains any transgenic events,

dimensions.name: seed_processing.material_fulfillment_groups
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Material Fullfillment Groups
dimensions.description: Material fulfillment groups in the Line Advancement Plan set entries are designated user groups responsible for managing physical inventory and fulfilling material requests within the materials marketplace.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.no_of_plots_assigned
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Plots Assigned
dimensions.description: The count of entries associated with the set. Unless a set is assigned to a field or plot or entryid, this will be null

dimensions.name: seed_processing.set_created_date
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Set Creation Date
dimensions.description: It is date of set creation. Returns a stringified date in UTC format.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.entry_number
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Entry Number
dimensions.description: The entrys order in the layout. This number is used to uniquely identify entries within a set. It is unique only within the scope of that specific set and is assigned sequentially starting from 1 up to the total number of entries in the set.  Generic entry numbers do not have any inherent business meaning or guaranteed relation to other identifiers

dimensions.name: seed_processing.product_type
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Product Type
dimensions.description: It is Material category like lot, seed, inventory, catalog etc

dimensions.name: seed_processing.entry_sequence_number
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Entry Sequence Number
dimensions.description: It is sequence order of Entry IDs in the layout .This number describes the order in which an entry should be placed in its layout. It is determined based on instructions from randomization (for trial sets) or by the nursery row pattern service (for production sets).  The sequence number indicates the placement direction and helps in constructing the layout on a map

dimensions.name: seed_processing.set_type
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Set Type
dimensions.description: It is an name given to make it more readable. Example values are Simple, Trial, Production

dimensions.name: seed_processing.population_name
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Population Name
dimensions.description: A population name refers to the designation given to a group of germplasm that is created during the breeding process.  Specifically, it is used to identify the progeny in the Material Marketplace, where users can see details such as the Population Name, Male Parent, and Female Parent data fields.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.material_type
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Material Type
dimensions.description: It is an Experiment Design name or also known as randomization Strategy Code

dimensions.name: seed_processing.germplasm_group_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Germplasm Group ID
dimensions.description: It is a group associated to this germplasm.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.capacity_request_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Capacity Request ID
dimensions.description: This is a system generated unique identifier created upon creation of a capacity request in the Velocity application

dimensions.name: seed_processing.experiment_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Experiment ID
dimensions.description: An Experiment ID in Velocity is a unique identifier assigned to each experiment.  It helps in organizing and managing experiments within the application, allowing users to easily reference and track specific experiments.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.is_template
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Is Template
dimensions.description: This tells is the LAP is generated using the template. True means yes it is generated using template. False means no is it not generated through use of template

dimensions.name: seed_processing.lap_owners
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing LAP Owners
dimensions.description: In the context of the Line Advancement Application, owners are individuals responsible for the request.  The owner and the requester can be the same person, but there must be at least one owner per request.  The application allows for multiple owners by entering additional names in the Owner field or by selecting a User group in the Owner Group field.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.lap_owner_groups
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing LAP Owner Groups
dimensions.description: An owners group refers to a group of individuals who have been designated as owners of a user group.  Recording the owners group at the LAP level is important because it helps ensure that all relevant stakeholders are identified and can be held accountable for the request.  Having a clear record of ownership allows for better communication, collaboration, and tracking of responsibilities throughout the process.  Additionally, it ensures that the request is managed effectively and that all necessary parties are informed.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.pollination_parent_type
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Pollination Parent Type
dimensions.description: This indicates the type of parent used in the pollination process.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.progeny_type
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Progeny Type
dimensions.description: This indicates the type of progeny.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.created_by_user
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Created By User
dimensions.description: The Created By User in the Line Advancement Plan refers to the individual or system account that initiated the creation of a specific entry within the plan.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.created_date
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Created Date
dimensions.description: The Created Date in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the specific date when an entry was first created, providing a timeline for tracking the addition of data within the system.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.modified_by_user
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Modified By User
dimensions.description: The Modified By User in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the individual or system account responsible for the most recent changes made to an entry, ensuring accountability in data management.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.modified_date
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Modified Date
dimensions.description: The Modified Date in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the specific date when an entry was last updated or changed.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.pollination_event_status
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Pollination Event Status
dimensions.description: The pollination event status in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the current state of a pollination event, helping to track its progress from creation to completion.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.harvest_event_status
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Harvest Event Status
dimensions.description: The harvest event status in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the current state of a harvest event, helping to track its progress from initiation to completion.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.pollination_intentid
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Pollination Intent ID
dimensions.description: The pollination intent id in the Line Advancement Plan serves as a unique identifier for tracking and managing specific pollination activities associated with each entry.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.progeny
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Progeny
dimensions.description: The progeny in the Line Advancement Plan refers to the offspring generated from specific breeding activities, which are tracked and managed within the plan to assess their development and characteristics.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.male_parent
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Male Parent
dimensions.description: The male parent refers to the male entity used in breeding activities, which contributes genetic material to the offspring being tracked and managed within the plan.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.female_parent
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Female Parent
dimensions.description: The female parent refers to the female entity used in breeding activities, which provides genetic material to the offspring being tracked and managed within the plan.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.is_placeholder
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Is Placeholder
dimensions.description: This indicates whether the entry is a placeholder.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.anticipated_pollination_attempts
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Anticipated Pollination Attempts
dimensions.description: The Anticipated Pollination Attempts refers to the number of times you plan to pollinate each plant or set entry to achieve your desired harvest target quantity.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.harvest_target_quantity
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Harvest Target Quantity
dimensions.description: The harvest target quantity refers to the specific amount of plant material or flowers that you aim to collect from a breeding plan during the harvest phase.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.harvest_target_quantity_uom_uode
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Harvest Target Quantity UOM
dimensions.description: The Harvest Target Quantity UOM refers to the unit of measurement used to specify the desired amount of plant material or flowers you aim to collect during the harvest phase.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.harvest_method
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Harvest Method
dimensions.description: The Harvest Method refers to the various approaches for collecting plants during the harvest phase, which include Bulk, Select, Select & Bulk and Bulk Group.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.harvest_selections
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Harvest Selections
dimensions.description: Harvest Selections refers to the number of individual plants or entries that you plan to select for harvesting based on specific criteria.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.blocks
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Blocks
dimensions.description: Blocks are used to separate intents and create multiple sets, allowing for organized management of harvesting plans.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.block_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Block ID
dimensions.description: Block ID is a unique identifier for each block, facilitating effective management and referencing of specific blocks within the application.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.reciprocal_of_intent_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Reciprocal of Intent ID
dimensions.description: The Reciprocal of Intent ID is a unique identifier for tracking reciprocal pollination events between two plants, facilitating effective management of these intents within the application.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.male_block
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Male Block
dimensions.description: The Male Block is a designated section for organizing and managing male plant intents, ensuring effective tracking of male contributions in the breeding process.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.male_block_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Male Block ID
dimensions.description: The Male Block ID is a unique identifier for a specific block that organizes and manages male plant intents, facilitating effective tracking of male contributions in the breeding process.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.male_set_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Male Set ID
dimensions.description: The Male Set ID is a unique identifier for a specific set that organizes and manages male plant intents, essential for tracking male contributions in the breeding process.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.planting_cross_instrn_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Planting Cross Instruction ID
dimensions.description: Planting Cross Instruction ID is a unique identifier that outlines the guidelines for planting crosses

dimensions.name: seed_processing.lap_cross_type
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing LAP Cross Type
dimensions.description: The LAP Cross Type refers to the specific category of cross used in breeding, including Self, Test, and Development crosses, which guide the breeding strategy and management of plant breeding activities.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.reciprocal_cross
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Reciprocal Cross
dimensions.description: Determines if the PCI will have reciprocal crosses

dimensions.name: seed_processing.pollination_operations
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Pollination Operations
dimensions.description: Determines pollination operation of the PCI

dimensions.name: seed_processing.cross_type_pattern
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Cross Type Pattern
dimensions.description: Determines the cross type pattern of the PCI

dimensions.name: seed_processing.icb
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing ICB
dimensions.description: Determines if PCI supports multiple, different male parents within a block

dimensions.name: seed_processing.custom_row_pattern
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Custom Row Pattern
dimensions.description: Determines the gender layout of a custom pattern

dimensions.name: seed_processing.custom_pattern_pairing
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Custom Pattern Pairing
dimensions.description: Determines which entries correspond with each other

dimensions.name: seed_processing.prcsg_intent_id
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Processing Intent ID
dimensions.description: The Processing Intent ID is a unique identifier used to track and manage processing activities related to specific breeding intents.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.keep_quantity_min
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Keep Quantity Min
dimensions.description: The Keep Quantity Min is the minimum amount of seeds or materials that must be retained for each breeding intent to ensure sufficient availability for processing or evaluation.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.keep_quantity_max
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Keep Quantity Max
dimensions.description: The Keep Quantity Max is the maximum amount of seeds or materials that can be retained for each breeding intent to effectively manage inventory while ensuring availability for processing or evaluation.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.keep_quantity_uom_code
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Keep Quantity UOM
dimensions.description: The Keep Quantity UOM code in the Line Advancement Plan specifies the unit of measure used for quantifying the seeds or materials retained for each breeding intent.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.treatment_ids
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Treatment ID
dimensions.description: The treatment IDs are unique identifiers assigned to specific treatments or breeding intents within the plan.

dimensions.name: seed_processing.unprocessed_inventory_count
dimensions.title: Shellmatic Seed Processing Unprocessed Inventory
dimensions.description: The unprocessed inventory count is the number of inventories that have not yet been processed

cubes.name: seed_processing_ytp
cubes.title: YTP Seed Processing
cubes.description: Seed processing is the first step in the process of preparing seeds for planting post harvest.  The main goal is to enhance seed quality while also gathering quantity and sizing data.  This process can include shelling, cleaning, sorting, sizing, counting and treating seed. The current source for seed information is YTP. YTP is  IT system that enables overall Seed Processing system

dimensions.name: seed_processing_ytp.batch_packet_barcode
dimensions.title: YTP Seed Processing Batch Packet Barcode
dimensions.description: It is an alphanumeric unique combination of 24 characters generated in ascending order. It is a barocde applied to the packets corresponding to when the genetic material is distributed into packets from the source batch. It is displayed as 'P00000000879560012886300'. In the mactracker_nsp table, if the barcode starts with P, source is Midas. If the barcode is fully numeric, source is velocity.

dimensions.name: seed_processing_ytp.machine_location
dimensions.title: YTP Seed Processing Machine Location
dimensions.description: This is the location of the machine. Is a character entity of fixed length, with an upper limit of 3 characters. It is an indicator of where the batch was processed. (3 letter code of physical machine location). It is displayed as a 3 character code from the mactracker_location_lookup table for valid values. It is generated from the shellmatic application. It is not empty

dimensions.name: seed_processing_ytp.machine_serial
dimensions.title: YTP Seed Processing Machine Serial
dimensions.description: This is the serial of the machine.

dimensions.name: seed_processing_ytp.batch_type
dimensions.title: YTP Seed Processing Batch Type
dimensions.description: This is the type of the batch.

This catalog share the complete information of all the semantic views available to a user along with other meta data like Semantic Catalog, Dimension Name, Attribute Type, Dimension Title, SQL Expression, Is it Primary Key, Dimension Data Type, Table Name, Cube Description, Cube Title, Cube Data Source, Semantic View Name,  Semantic View Title, Semantic View Description, Visible in Semantic View, Relationship Path, Semantic View Folder Name.

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.dimension_type

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.cube_sql_table

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.cube_description
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Cube Description
dimensions.description: It is description about a cube that contributes towards a semantic view in cube.dev

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.cube_title
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Cube Title
dimensions.description: It is label or name provided by Business User to a cube in cube.dev

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.cube_data_source
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Cube Data Source
dimensions.description: It is label or name provided data source in cube.dev. For e.g. Breeding data sources, Veg data sources.

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.view_name
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Semantic View Name
dimensions.description: Technical Name of a semantic view in a Cube.dev semantic tool

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.view_title
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Semantic View Title
dimensions.description: It is label or name given to Semantic View Name to map to Business Context. It is provided by Business Users

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.view_description
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Semantic View Description
dimensions.description: It is description about a Semantic View Name to map to Business Context. It is provided by Business Users

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.visible_in_view
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog Visible in Semantic View
dimensions.description: It is flag that indicates if a dimension is enables to access through any Semantic View

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.join_path

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.view_folder_name

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.adapt_environment

dimensions.description: This shows the ADAPT Environment associated to the Semantic Catalog

dimensions.name: semantic_catalog.adapt_environment_url
dimensions.title: Semantic Catalog ADAPT URL
dimensions.description: This shows the ADAPT Environment URL associated to the Semantic Catalog

measures.name: traitintegration.Count_of_projects
measures.title: Trait Integration Count of Projects
measures.description: Count of distinct projects

measures.name: traitintegration.Count_of_discarded_plot
measures.title: Trait Integration Count of Discarded Plot

measures.name: traitintegration.seed_qty_produced
measures.title: Trait Integration Seed Quantity Produced

cubes.name: vegetable_field_trials
cubes.title: Vegetable Field Trials
cubes.description: This vegetable field trial business view enables environmental clustering analysis. It is a repetition within a trial, planted in a specific field.The data view includes repetitions, fields, and trials only when the GPS coordinates for the field are accurately captured (with at least four points forming a valid polygon).

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.entryid
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Entry ID
dimensions.description: This is a system generated unique identifier created upon creation of an experiment set entry in the Velocity application.  An Experiment set entry id is created only upon creation of a capacity request. An Experiment set entry id is also called as Entry ID. Entry ID is same as Entity ID. It is also called as plot_id or plot id in the FTS application

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.protocolid
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Protocol ID
dimensions.description: It is a system generated unique identifier for this protocol. Protocol is a central location where all of your plans and operational instructions are linked together, serving as a starting point for your workflow in Velocity.  It consists of a collection of templates from various applications that can be copied as needed to carry out different workflows.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.protocol_name

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.setid
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Set ID
dimensions.description: A Set ID refers to the unique identifier for a planned planting or grow-out of material in a field or controlled environment.  Each set can consist of sub-units called entries, which may contain different materials.  The Set ID is essential for tracking and managing these plantings effectively

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.germplasmid
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: A Germplasm ID is a unique identifier assigned to a specific germplasm, which is a collection of genetic resources for an organism.  This ID helps in tracking and managing genetic materials, ensuring that each germplasm can be accurately referenced in databases and inventories.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.velmat_material_id

dimensions.description: A Material ID in Velocity is a globally unique identifier for a Velocity material. This could refer to an inventory barcode, lot ID,  or catalog item ID, depending on whether it pertains to an inventory, lot, or catalog item.
