dimensions.description: User Groups are defined by business and consist of users from similar roles, squads, or units.  They enable visibility, sharing, and editing of trials among squad and unit members, facilitating collaboration and accountability

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.relativematurity
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials RM
dimensions.description: Relative Maturity (RM) is a measurement in agronomy that assists farmers in determining which hybrids to use for their crops with the RM often tied to yield.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.sets_material_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Inventory ID
dimensions.description: An inventory ID is typically a unique identifier assigned to a specific inventory item within a system like MIDAS. It helps in tracking and managing inventory accurately.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.populationid
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Population ID
dimensions.description: a Population ID refers to a unique identifier assigned to a specific Population. This ID helps in managing and tracking the associated data of that Population

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.set_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Set Name
dimensions.description: A set name refers to the title given to a planned planting or grow out of material in a field or controlled environment.  Each set can be composed of sub-units called entries (such as plots, plants, or pots), and the set name helps to identify and manage these groupings effectively.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.linetype
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Line Type
dimensions.description: It is legacy piece of data that can be HYBRID, FINISHED, CODED, or SEGPOP.  This typically refers to the specific genetic lines being used in the breeding process. Different line types may have distinct genetic backgrounds and traits.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.linecode
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Line Code
dimensions.description: It is an user defined name applied to a given germplasm

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.pedigree
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Pedigree
dimensions.description: Pedigree refers to a concatenated value that includes components such as Origin, Lineage or Line Code, and Precommercial name. It is string version of parental ancestry

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.geneticmaterialid
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Genetic Material ID
dimensions.description: This captures midas genetic material id

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.rep
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Repition
dimensions.description: It indicates how many times a specific activity or set of entries is performed or recorded

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.iscontrol
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Is Control
dimensions.description: Flag to indicate the controltypes. True means controltype exis

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.fts_germplasmid
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials FTS Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: The Germplasm resource identifier from FTS application

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.sets_material_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Set Material Name
dimensions.description: It is material name of the set. a material name typically refers to the name associated with a specific material that used in the set. This could be linked to the Material ID, which is a globally unique identifier for a Velocity material, such as an inventory barcode, lot ID, or catalog item ID.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.experiment_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Experiment Name
dimensions.description: An experiment name refers to the specific title or identifier given to a particular experiment.  This name helps in organizing and referencing the experiment within the system. It is part of the structured design that allows users to gather and analyze data effectively.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.treatmentnumber
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Treatment Number
dimensions.description: It is a treatment number. A treatment number is a unique identifier used to identify all treatment lines that are components of one treatment in the context of chemical applications. In the Velocity system, treatment numbers must start at 1 and follow a continuous sequence (e.g., 1, 2, 3, 4).  This numbering is important for organizing and managing treatments effectively.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.controltypes_coded
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Control Types Codes

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.analysismodeltype
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Analysis Model Type
dimensions.description: Type of analysis model used

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.analysismodelsubtype
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Analysis Model Sub Type
dimensions.description: This provides the sub type of the Analysis model used

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.treatment_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Treatment ID
dimensions.description: It is list of Seed Treatment Applications. A Treatment ID is the globally unique identifier for a Velocity experimental treatment.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.catalog_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Catalog ID
dimensions.description: A Catalog ID is a unique identifier generated by the Velocity system for a specific catalog record.  It is used to describe a unique material and the attributes associated with that material, helping to tie together all the lots and inventories that represent the same material

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.catalog_seed_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Catalog Seed Type
dimensions.description: The seed type of the catalog. For example Internal Seed, Commercial Check

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.block_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Block ID
dimensions.description: Experiment’s unique identifier. Represents test_set_id in Midas

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.block_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Block Name
dimensions.description: A non-unique string used to identify the experimental set. Represents test set name for records from FTS.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.deactivationreason_coded
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Entry Deactivation Reason Code
dimensions.description: A deactivation reason is a justification provided by the user when they deactivate plot or entry.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.p360_product_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials p360 Product ID
dimensions.description: Describes the product 360 product identifier for velocity experiments. If the plants in the experiment are associated to a product intended to sell, this field will have values

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.source_str
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Source String
dimensions.description: The Test Set name corresponding to when the genetic material was produced.source_str from midas for a genetic material, business logic stored in text box based on linecode of parents

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.is_transgenic
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Is Trangenic
dimensions.description: Flag indicating if the germplasm contains a transgenic event

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.transgenic_events
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Transgenic Events
dimensions.description: List of transgenic events Transgenic Events represent foreign DNA from usually the same species inserted purposefully into a new speciemen through a vector

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.constructs
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Constructs
dimensions.description: This field contains the identities of the constructs used in the transformation process, provided the germplasm contains any transgenic events,

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.material_fulfillment_groups
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Material Fullfillment Groups

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.no_of_plots_assigned
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Plots Assigned
dimensions.description: The count of entries associated with the set. Unless a set is assigned to a field or plot or entryid, this will be null

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.set_created_date
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Set Creation Date
dimensions.description: It is date of set creation. Returns a stringified date in UTC format.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.entry_number
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Entry Number
dimensions.description: The entrys order in the layout. This number is used to uniquely identify entries within a set. It is unique only within the scope of that specific set and is assigned sequentially starting from 1 up to the total number of entries in the set.  Generic entry numbers do not have any inherent business meaning or guaranteed relation to other identifiers

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.experiment_design
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Experiment Design
dimensions.description: It is an Experiment Design name or also known as randomization Strategy Code

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.product_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Product Type
dimensions.description: It is Material category like lot, seed, inventory, catalog etc

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.entry_sequence_number
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Entry Sequence Number
dimensions.description: It is sequence order of Entry IDs in the layout .This number describes the order in which an entry should be placed in its layout. It is determined based on instructions from randomization (for trial sets) or by the nursery row pattern service (for production sets).  The sequence number indicates the placement direction and helps in constructing the layout on a map

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.set_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Set Type
dimensions.description: It is an name given to make it more readable. Example values are Simple, Trial, Production

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.population_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Population Name
dimensions.description: A population name refers to the designation given to a group of germplasm that is created during the breeding process.  Specifically, it is used to identify the progeny in the Material Marketplace, where users can see details such as the Population Name, Male Parent, and Female Parent data fields.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.material_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Material Type
dimensions.description: It is an Experiment Design name or also known as randomization Strategy Code

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.germplasm_group_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Germplasm Group ID
dimensions.description: It is a group associated to this germplasm.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.experiment_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Experiment ID
dimensions.description: An Experiment ID in Velocity is a unique identifier assigned to each experiment.  It helps in organizing and managing experiments within the application, allowing users to easily reference and track specific experiments.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.capacity_request_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Capacity Request ID
dimensions.description: The Capacity Request ID in Velocity is a unique identifier assigned to each capacity request made within the Capacity Request workflow in the Velocity application This ID helps users track and manage their requests effectively throughout the process.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.harvest_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Harvest Type
dimensions.description: This refers to the method or technique used to gather crops from the field once they have reached maturity in the context of capacity requests It also shows the default harvest type of the track intent or the rep’s harvest type. For example Crop Yield Harvest, Hand - Yield, Yield Monitor, Seed Harvest,  Crop Destruct, Machine - Yield, Silage, Seed Yield Harvest, Crop Harvest, Veg Harvest, Cut Bags, Open Pollination

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.crop_material_stage
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Crop Stage Name
dimensions.description: It specific phase or step within the product development pipeline for example Commercial,Pre-Commercial 0, Pre-Commercial 2,Pre-Commercial 2.5, Pre-Commercial 3,Pre-Commercial 4, Mixed PCM Stages, Level 1, Level 2, Level 4, Entry Level, Screening 0,Screening 1,Screening 2, Screening 2 - Prep, Screening 2 - Test,Germplasm Development, Pipeline Unrelated etc

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.season
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Season
dimensions.description: This indicates the name of the growing season.It refers to a defined timeframe within which specific activities or operations are planned or executed Example Summer,Autumn, Winter, Spring, Winter in the country Brazil is called as Safrinha, Summer in the country Brazil is called as Verao

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.trial_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Trail Type
dimensions.description: It is an experiment trial type. For example Research Trial, Field Trial, Observation, Commercial Trial - Market Development, Nursery, Field Trial - Seed Treatment, Seed Production, Yield Trial, Commercial Trial, Tech Dev / Research Trial, Performance - Validation, Performance - Adaptability, Commercial Trial - Third Party, Commercial Trial - University, Agronomy / Commercial Trial, Value-Added, Recommendation, Commercial Trial - Competitor Plot, Commercial Trial - Side by Side, Market Dev / Research Trial, Commercial Trial - FTN and/or Field Scale Spatial

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.trial_intent
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Trail Intent
dimensions.description: In the Capacity Request application, the Trial Intent refers to the description of the purpose of the trial being conducted.  This field allows users to specify the objective or goal of their experimental or seed production workflows.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.maturity
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Maturity
dimensions.description: It is a value or a range which represents maturity of a plant in terms which are product-specific and which help determine optimal harvest. Average relative maturity of products in the experiment

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.crops
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Crops
dimensions.description: The name of the crop. For example Corn, Rice, Cotton, Soybeans etc. It refers to the specific type of crop that you are requesting to be used for your experimental or seed production workflows.  When filling out a capacity request, you will need to specify the crop in the designated field, which is essential for the planning and allocation of resources.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.planting_year
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Planting Year
dimensions.description: This is the year when the plot or entryid will be planted. It is called Planting year of a plot or an entry

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.total_plots
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Total Plots
dimensions.description: In the Capacity Request application, the total plots field is calculated based on the following formula: Total Plots = Seed Products * Reps/site * Non-Seed product treatments + border plots. This calculation helps determine the number of plots required for your request based on the specified parameters.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.plots_per_site
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Plots per site
dimensions.description: In the context of Capacity Requests, plots per sites refers to the specific allocation of planting areas (or plots) that are designated for use at various sites.  Each site can have multiple plots, and the capacity request helps in managing and organizing these plots based on the requirements for planting. This generally refers to the overall plots associated with a specific site, which can encompass multiple subsites.  It represents the totality of plots within a defined geographical area or farm.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.plots_per_internal_site
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Plots per internal site
dimensions.description: In the context of the Capacity Request application, plots per internal sites refers to the specific allocation of plots or growing areas designated within the internal sites for planting crops.  Each internal site can have multiple plots, and the Capacity Request helps in estimating and managing the number of plots needed based on the planned crop planting. This term usually pertains to plots that are managed or categorized within the internal framework of the application.  Internal sites may refer to subsites that are part of a larger site, focusing on specific areas or crops within that site.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.plots_per_external_site
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Plots per external site
dimensions.description: In the context of Capacity Requests, plots per external sites  typically refers to the allocation or distribution of plots that are designated for use at external locations or sites outside of the primary operational area. This likely refers to plots that are associated with external locations or farms that are not part of the internal organizational structure.  These could be sites that are managed externally or are part of a different operational framework.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Capacity Request Name
dimensions.description: The Capacity Request Name is a unique identifier that user enter for the specific project upon creation of capacity request  within the Capacity Request tab in the Velocity application. It is an unique name that you enter specifically for the capacity request itself.  The Request Name is used to identify the capacity request within the application and is required for submission. This can not be empty

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.previous_crop
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Previous Crop
dimensions.description: This records the previous crop in the field

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.originating_country
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Originating Country
dimensions.description: The term Originating Country typically refers to the country where a particular material or product is produced or sourced from. In the context of seed materials,  it indicates the country of origin for the seeds listed in the inventory or catalog.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.specialty_requirements
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Speciality Requirements
dimensions.description: Specialty requirements refer to specific conditions or documentation that may be necessary for the request.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.status
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Status
dimensions.description: The indicates the current condition of a capacity request created in the Velocity table. For example Draft,  Pending Approval, Cancelled, Completed, Planning, Assigned, Exception Process, Deprioritized, Need More Data, Ready for Set Creation

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.rows_per_plot
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Rows per plot
dimensions.description: Rows per Plot refers to the number of rows that are designated for each plot within a planting session.  This metric is crucial for ensuring that the planting session is validated correctly, particularly in relation to the capacity request. When setting up a capacity request, it's important to ensure that the Rows per Plot aligns with the packet entry ratio, as discrepancies can lead to errors during validation.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.approval_flag
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Approval Flag
dimensions.description: The true indicates the submitted capacity request has been approved, false indicates the submitted capacity request is not approved

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.border_plots
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Border Plots
dimensions.description: This gives the number of border plots

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.checks
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Checks
dimensions.description: The number of commercial Checks on the Capacity Request. Checks are defined as Bayer or Competitor products  that are added to experimental or observational trials to either compare against trial entries or  normalize data for environment or year effects. Based on the trial requirements, different types of checks are utilized.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.cross_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Cross Type
dimensions.description: In crop science, cross type refers to the method of pollination and breeding used to produce new plant varieties.  It involves the intentional crossing of different plant lines or varieties to achieve specific traits or improvements in the offspring. Some of the values are Back Cross,Dev Cross, Self, Sibling Cross, Test Cross, Stack Cross

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.cycle_time
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Cycle Time
dimensions.description: It is number of days that typically refers to the duration of a complete growth cycle of a plant from planting to harvest.  This term is essential for understanding the timing of agricultural practices and can vary significantly among different crops

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.description
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Capacity Description
dimensions.description: This is the description that is captured on the capacity request upon creation in the Velocity application.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.footprint
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Footprint
dimensions.description: The will provide the name that appears on the footprint

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.num_of_bayer_growing_sites
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Bayer Growing Sites
dimensions.description: This is gives information about number of the Bayer internal sites associated to the capacity request

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.num_of_non_bayer_growing_sites
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Non Bayer Growing Sites
dimensions.description: This is gives information about number of the external sites associated to the capacity request.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.owner_groups
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Owner Groups
dimensions.description: An owners group refers to a group of individuals who have been designated as owners of a user group.  Recording the owners group in the capacity request is important because it helps ensure that all relevant stakeholders are identified and can be held accountable for the request.  Having a clear record of ownership allows for better communication, collaboration, and tracking of responsibilities throughout the process.  Additionally, it ensures that the request is managed effectively and that all necessary parties are informed.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.owners
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Owners
dimensions.description: In the context of the Capacity Request application, owners are individuals responsible for the request.  The owner and the requester can be the same person, but there must be at least one owner per request.  The application allows for multiple owners by entering additional names in the Owner field or by selecting a User group in the Owner Group field.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.pollination_layout
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Pollination Layout
dimensions.description: It generally refers to the arrangement or strategy used for pollination in plant breeding.  This can include the selection of parent plants, the method of pollination (such as open, assisted, or controlled), and the tracking of reciprocal crosses.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.reps_per_site
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Reps per site
dimensions.description: The term reps_per_site in the context of the Capacity Request application typically refers to the number of replicates or copies of a specific entry that are associated with a site.  This concept is similar to how reps are used in experimental design, where a set of entries can have multiple replicates to ensure reliability and accuracy in data collection.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.requested_icb_male
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Requested ICB Male
dimensions.description: It is the Requested ICB Male information on the Capacity Request

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.requester
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Requester
dimensions.description: In the context of the Capacity Request application, the requester is the individual who initiates the request for capacity

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.total_area
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Total Area
dimensions.description: The total area field in the Capacity Request workflow in Velocity is calculated based on information pulled from the footprint.  This data is essential for making full area calculations, which will be used in the Allocate Environment process.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.total_area_uom
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Total Area UOM
dimensions.description: The Unit Of Measure associated with Total Area

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.total_num_of_bayer_sites
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Total Bayer Sites
dimensions.description: The Total Bayer Sites field in the Capacity Request application is used to specify the number of sites that are owned or operated by Bayer where the capacity request is applicable.  This field helps in assessing the overall capacity needs and planning for experiments or production workflows outside of Bayer's facilities.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.total_num_of_non_bayer_sites
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Total Non Bayer Sites
dimensions.description: The Total Non-Bayer Sites field in the Capacity Request application is used to specify the number of sites that are not owned or operated by Bayer where the capacity request is applicable.  This field helps in assessing the overall capacity needs and planning for experiments or production workflows outside of Bayer's facilities.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.induced_treatments
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Induced Treatments
dimensions.description: This refers to various methods used to create genetic variation or enhance specific traits in plants through controlled interventions.  These treatments can help breeders develop new varieties with desirable characteristics, such as improved yield, disease resistance, or environmental adaptability. For example Tar Spot, Goss's Bacterial Wilt, Fusarium Ear Rot, Nitrogen - Fall Applied, Spray - Off Label Requirements - Post, Disease - Charcoal Rot, Disease - Gibberella Stalk Rot (Gsr)

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.disease_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Disease Type
dimensions.description: Refers to the classification of diseases that affect plants, typically based on their causal agents, symptoms, and the way they impact the crops. For example. COCHSA - Foot Rot, FUSASP - Fusarium spp., PYRNTE - Net blotch: barley, RAMUCC - Ramularia collo-cygni, RHYNSE - Leaf blotch: cereals, USTINH - Smut, loose: barley, COLLSP - Colletotrichum spp., FUSASP - Fusarium spp., MCPHSP - Macrophomina sp., PHYTMS - Phytophthora Root Rot, BIPOSP - Bipolaris sp,PENIOX - Root Rot, ALTEBA - Alternaria brassicae

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.total_sq_ft
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Total Sq Ft
dimensions.description: The total square footage area in the Capacity Request is calculated based on the selections made in the required fields across all sections, including the Inputs Tab.  This area is automatically computed and displayed in the Flats Total Area and Pots or Flats Total Area fields.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.project_ar
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Project AR
dimensions.description: In the context of a Capacity Request, the Project AR Name typically refers to a unique identifier used within a specific project or system,

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.entries
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Entries
dimensions.description: The entries are the number of plots assigned to the capacity request. This is planned but actual value could change at the entryid or plot or field

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.trait_stack_abbreviation
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Trait Stack Abbr.
dimensions.description: Shortened name of the trait stack. For example BR2, FSR, BLSB, ASR1,DER, FER, GLS, CONV etc

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.manufacturing_trait_code
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Manufacturing Trait
dimensions.description: Manufacturing Trait Code is a 3 letter code used as an internal identifier for trait stacks associated with corn products. This value is also embedded in the pre commercial product name, and the manufacturing name of the hybrid.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.submission_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Submission ID
dimensions.description: The submission ID on the capacity request is typically the unique identifier associated with a specific submission.  This ID is used to associate the capacity request with the protocol submission.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.submission_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Submission Name
dimensions.description: This provides name for the protocol submission

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.total_short_row_equivalent
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Total Short Row Equivalent
dimensions.description: A unit for estimation of seed production

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.non_seed_product_treatments
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Non Seed Product Treatments
dimensions.description: This captures the number of product treaments that are not related to seed

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.num_plants
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Total Plants
dimensions.description: The number of plants for the capacity request

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.organization
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Organization
dimensions.description: This is the Business units like Enterprise, Breeding, Market Development, Production Research, IADT. It is also called as Requesting Organization

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.region
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Region
dimensions.description: Region name for the Bayer Site located in like United States of America(US), LAS, North America, Canada, EME,Africa,Asia,Brazil,LAN

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.regional_hub
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Regional Hub
dimensions.description: Name of the hubs like Global, Africa, Asia, Europe, North America, South America, Latin America, Asia Pacific, Asia Africa, Middle East

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.market
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Market
dimensions.description: This describe Bayer’s market like WET, DRY, RM100,RM70, RM120

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.sub_market
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Sub Market
dimensions.description: This describe Bayer’s market like ME1, RM5.1_5.4, ME4_DRY_EAST_ST

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.rtdl_territory
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Environment RTDL Territory
dimensions.description: It gives information about RTDL Territory recorded at the environment level for each capacity request

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.site_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Site ID
dimensions.description: Typically refers to a specific location where research, trials, or breeding activities are conducted

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.sub_site_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Sub Site ID
dimensions.description: A subsite ID refers to the unique identifier associated with a subsite within a larger site or farm structure.  Subsites are typically smaller areas that can represent different fields or rotational crops within a farm.  The system allows users to find subsites by typing in their names, which helps in retrieving the corresponding feature ID without needing to know the ID itself.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.site_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Site Name
dimensions.description: In the context of the Bayer Sites, a site name refers to the specific designation given to a Bayer Site,  which is a geometry defining an area that can be characterized in the Characterize Bayer Sites (CBS) application.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.homesite_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Homesite Name
dimensions.description: It a readable name for associated homesite

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.l0_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials Country
dimensions.description: It defines the country in which the location resides. Global Geopolitical Admin Boundaries - Level 0.

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.l1_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials State
dimensions.description: It defines the state or province in which the location resides. Global Geopolitical Admin Boundaries - Level 1. It is also called as Province or Region

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.l2_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Field Trials County
dimensions.description: It defines the county in which the location resides. Global Geopolitical Admin Boundaries - Level 2. It is also called as District or Division

dimensions.name: velocity_field_trials.field_name

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.capacity_request_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Capacity Request ID
dimensions.description: The Capacity Request ID in Velocity is a unique identifier assigned to each capacity request made within the Capacity Request workflow in the Velocity application This ID helps users track and manage their requests effectively throughout the process.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.harvest_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Harvest Type
dimensions.description: This refers to the method or technique used to gather crops from the field once they have reached maturity in the context of capacity requests It also shows the default harvest type of the track intent or the rep’s harvest type. For example Crop Yield Harvest, Hand - Yield, Yield Monitor, Seed Harvest,  Crop Destruct, Machine - Yield, Silage, Seed Yield Harvest, Crop Harvest, Veg Harvest, Cut Bags, Open Pollination

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.crop_material_stage
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Crop Stage Name
dimensions.description: It specific phase or step within the product development pipeline for example Commercial,Pre-Commercial 0, Pre-Commercial 2,Pre-Commercial 2.5, Pre-Commercial 3,Pre-Commercial 4, Mixed PCM Stages, Level 1, Level 2, Level 4, Entry Level, Screening 0,Screening 1,Screening 2, Screening 2 - Prep, Screening 2 - Test,Germplasm Development, Pipeline Unrelated etc

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.season
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Season
dimensions.description: This indicates the name of the growing season.It refers to a defined timeframe within which specific activities or operations are planned or executed Example Summer,Autumn, Winter, Spring, Winter in the country Brazil is called as Safrinha, Summer in the country Brazil is called as Verao

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.trial_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Trail Type
dimensions.description: It is an experiment trial type. For example Research Trial, Field Trial, Observation, Commercial Trial - Market Development, Nursery, Field Trial - Seed Treatment, Seed Production, Yield Trial, Commercial Trial, Tech Dev / Research Trial, Performance - Validation, Performance - Adaptability, Commercial Trial - Third Party, Commercial Trial - University, Agronomy / Commercial Trial, Value-Added, Recommendation, Commercial Trial - Competitor Plot, Commercial Trial - Side by Side, Market Dev / Research Trial, Commercial Trial - FTN and/or Field Scale Spatial

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.trial_intent
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Trail Intent
dimensions.description: In the Capacity Request application, the Trial Intent refers to the description of the purpose of the trial being conducted.  This field allows users to specify the objective or goal of their experimental or seed production workflows.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.maturity
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Maturity
dimensions.description: It is a value or a range which represents maturity of a plant in terms which are product-specific and which help determine optimal harvest. Average relative maturity of products in the experiment

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.crops
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Crops
dimensions.description: The name of the crop. For example Corn, Rice, Cotton, Soybeans etc. It refers to the specific type of crop that you are requesting to be used for your experimental or seed production workflows.  When filling out a capacity request, you will need to specify the crop in the designated field, which is essential for the planning and allocation of resources.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.planting_year
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Planting Year
dimensions.description: This is the year when the plot or entryid will be planted. It is called Planting year of a plot or an entry

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.total_plots
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Total Plots
dimensions.description: In the Capacity Request application, the total plots field is calculated based on the following formula: Total Plots = Seed Products * Reps/site * Non-Seed product treatments + border plots. This calculation helps determine the number of plots required for your request based on the specified parameters.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.plots_per_site
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Plots per site
dimensions.description: In the context of Capacity Requests, plots per sites refers to the specific allocation of planting areas (or plots) that are designated for use at various sites.  Each site can have multiple plots, and the capacity request helps in managing and organizing these plots based on the requirements for planting. This generally refers to the overall plots associated with a specific site, which can encompass multiple subsites.  It represents the totality of plots within a defined geographical area or farm.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.plots_per_internal_site
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Plots per internal site
dimensions.description: In the context of the Capacity Request application, plots per internal sites refers to the specific allocation of plots or growing areas designated within the internal sites for planting crops.  Each internal site can have multiple plots, and the Capacity Request helps in estimating and managing the number of plots needed based on the planned crop planting. This term usually pertains to plots that are managed or categorized within the internal framework of the application.  Internal sites may refer to subsites that are part of a larger site, focusing on specific areas or crops within that site.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.plots_per_external_site
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Plots per external site
dimensions.description: In the context of Capacity Requests, plots per external sites  typically refers to the allocation or distribution of plots that are designated for use at external locations or sites outside of the primary operational area. This likely refers to plots that are associated with external locations or farms that are not part of the internal organizational structure.  These could be sites that are managed externally or are part of a different operational framework.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.name
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Capacity Request Name
dimensions.description: The Capacity Request Name is a unique identifier that user enter for the specific project upon creation of capacity request  within the Capacity Request tab in the Velocity application. It is an unique name that you enter specifically for the capacity request itself.  The Request Name is used to identify the capacity request within the application and is required for submission. This can not be empty

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.previous_crop
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Previous Crop
dimensions.description: This records the previous crop in the field

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.originating_country
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Originating Country
dimensions.description: The term Originating Country typically refers to the country where a particular material or product is produced or sourced from. In the context of seed materials,  it indicates the country of origin for the seeds listed in the inventory or catalog.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.specialty_requirements
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Speciality Requirements
dimensions.description: Specialty requirements refer to specific conditions or documentation that may be necessary for the request.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.status
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Status
dimensions.description: The indicates the current condition of a capacity request created in the Velocity table. For example Draft,  Pending Approval, Cancelled, Completed, Planning, Assigned, Exception Process, Deprioritized, Need More Data, Ready for Set Creation

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.rows_per_plot
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Rows per plot
dimensions.description: Rows per Plot refers to the number of rows that are designated for each plot within a planting session.  This metric is crucial for ensuring that the planting session is validated correctly, particularly in relation to the capacity request. When setting up a capacity request, it's important to ensure that the Rows per Plot aligns with the packet entry ratio, as discrepancies can lead to errors during validation.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.approval_flag
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Approval Flag
dimensions.description: The true indicates the submitted capacity request has been approved, false indicates the submitted capacity request is not approved

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.border_plots
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Border Plots
dimensions.description: This gives the number of border plots

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.checks
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Checks
dimensions.description: The number of commercial Checks on the Capacity Request. Checks are defined as Bayer or Competitor products  that are added to experimental or observational trials to either compare against trial entries or  normalize data for environment or year effects. Based on the trial requirements, different types of checks are utilized.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.cross_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Cross Type
dimensions.description: In crop science, cross type refers to the method of pollination and breeding used to produce new plant varieties.  It involves the intentional crossing of different plant lines or varieties to achieve specific traits or improvements in the offspring. Some of the values are Back Cross,Dev Cross, Self, Sibling Cross, Test Cross, Stack Cross

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.cycle_time
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Cycle Time
dimensions.description: It is number of days that typically refers to the duration of a complete growth cycle of a plant from planting to harvest.  This term is essential for understanding the timing of agricultural practices and can vary significantly among different crops

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.description
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Capacity Description
dimensions.description: This is the description that is captured on the capacity request upon creation in the Velocity application.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.footprint
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Footprint
dimensions.description: The will provide the name that appears on the footprint

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.num_of_bayer_growing_sites
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Bayer Growing Sites
dimensions.description: This is gives information about number of the Bayer internal sites associated to the capacity request

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.num_of_non_bayer_growing_sites
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Non Bayer Growing Sites
dimensions.description: This is gives information about number of the external sites associated to the capacity request.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.owner_groups
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Owner Groups
dimensions.description: An owners group refers to a group of individuals who have been designated as owners of a user group.  Recording the owners group in the capacity request is important because it helps ensure that all relevant stakeholders are identified and can be held accountable for the request.  Having a clear record of ownership allows for better communication, collaboration, and tracking of responsibilities throughout the process.  Additionally, it ensures that the request is managed effectively and that all necessary parties are informed.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.owners
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Owners
dimensions.description: In the context of the Capacity Request application, owners are individuals responsible for the request.  The owner and the requester can be the same person, but there must be at least one owner per request.  The application allows for multiple owners by entering additional names in the Owner field or by selecting a User group in the Owner Group field.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.pollination_layout
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Pollination Layout
dimensions.description: It generally refers to the arrangement or strategy used for pollination in plant breeding.  This can include the selection of parent plants, the method of pollination (such as open, assisted, or controlled), and the tracking of reciprocal crosses.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.reps_per_site
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Reps per site
dimensions.description: The term reps_per_site in the context of the Capacity Request application typically refers to the number of replicates or copies of a specific entry that are associated with a site.  This concept is similar to how reps are used in experimental design, where a set of entries can have multiple replicates to ensure reliability and accuracy in data collection.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.requested_icb_male
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Requested ICB Male
dimensions.description: It is the Requested ICB Male information on the Capacity Request

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.requester
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Requester
dimensions.description: In the context of the Capacity Request application, the requester is the individual who initiates the request for capacity

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.total_area
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Total Area
dimensions.description: The total area field in the Capacity Request workflow in Velocity is calculated based on information pulled from the footprint.  This data is essential for making full area calculations, which will be used in the Allocate Environment process.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.total_area_uom
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Total Area UOM
dimensions.description: The Unit Of Measure associated with Total Area

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.total_num_of_bayer_sites
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Total Bayer Sites
dimensions.description: The Total Bayer Sites field in the Capacity Request application is used to specify the number of sites that are owned or operated by Bayer where the capacity request is applicable.  This field helps in assessing the overall capacity needs and planning for experiments or production workflows outside of Bayer's facilities.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.total_num_of_non_bayer_sites
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Total Non Bayer Sites
dimensions.description: The Total Non-Bayer Sites field in the Capacity Request application is used to specify the number of sites that are not owned or operated by Bayer where the capacity request is applicable.  This field helps in assessing the overall capacity needs and planning for experiments or production workflows outside of Bayer's facilities.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.induced_treatments
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Induced Treatments
dimensions.description: This refers to various methods used to create genetic variation or enhance specific traits in plants through controlled interventions.  These treatments can help breeders develop new varieties with desirable characteristics, such as improved yield, disease resistance, or environmental adaptability. For example Tar Spot, Goss's Bacterial Wilt, Fusarium Ear Rot, Nitrogen - Fall Applied, Spray - Off Label Requirements - Post, Disease - Charcoal Rot, Disease - Gibberella Stalk Rot (Gsr)

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.disease_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Disease Type
dimensions.description: Refers to the classification of diseases that affect plants, typically based on their causal agents, symptoms, and the way they impact the crops. For example. COCHSA - Foot Rot, FUSASP - Fusarium spp., PYRNTE - Net blotch: barley, RAMUCC - Ramularia collo-cygni, RHYNSE - Leaf blotch: cereals, USTINH - Smut, loose: barley, COLLSP - Colletotrichum spp., FUSASP - Fusarium spp., MCPHSP - Macrophomina sp., PHYTMS - Phytophthora Root Rot, BIPOSP - Bipolaris sp,PENIOX - Root Rot, ALTEBA - Alternaria brassicae

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.total_sq_ft
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Total Sq Ft
dimensions.description: The total square footage area in the Capacity Request is calculated based on the selections made in the required fields across all sections, including the Inputs Tab.  This area is automatically computed and displayed in the Flats Total Area and Pots or Flats Total Area fields.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.project_ar
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Project AR
dimensions.description: In the context of a Capacity Request, the Project AR Name typically refers to a unique identifier used within a specific project or system,

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.experiment_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Experiment ID
dimensions.description: An Experiment ID in Velocity is a unique identifier assigned to each experiment.  It helps in organizing and managing experiments within the application, allowing users to easily reference and track specific experiments.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.entries
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Entries
dimensions.description: The entries are the number of plots assigned to the capacity request. This is planned but actual value could change at the entryid or plot or field

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.trait_stack_abbreviation
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Trait Stack Abbr.
dimensions.description: Shortened name of the trait stack. For example BR2, FSR, BLSB, ASR1,DER, FER, GLS, CONV etc

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.manufacturing_trait_code

dimensions.description: Manufacturing Trait Code is a 3 letter code used as an internal identifier for trait stacks associated with corn products. This value is also embedded in the pre commercial product name, and the manufacturing name of the hybrid.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.submission_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Submission ID
dimensions.description: The submission ID on the capacity request is typically the unique identifier associated with a specific submission.  This ID is used to associate the capacity request with the protocol submission.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.submission_name

dimensions.description: Name of the hubs like Global, Africa, Asia, Europe, North America, South America, Latin America, Asia Pacific, Asia Africa, Middle East

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.market
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Market
dimensions.description: This describe Bayer’s market like WET, DRY, RM100,RM70, RM120

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.sub_market
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Sub Market
dimensions.description: This describe Bayer’s market like ME1, RM5.1_5.4, ME4_DRY_EAST_ST

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.rtdl_territory
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Environment RTDL Territory
dimensions.description: It gives information about RTDL Territory recorded at the environment level for each capacity request

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.entry_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Entry ID
dimensions.description: This is a system generated unique identifier created upon creation of an experiment set entry in the Velocity application.  An Experiment set entry id is created only upon creation of a capacity request. An Experiment set entry id is also called as Entry ID. Entry ID is same as Entity ID. It is also called as plot_id or plot id in the FTS application

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.protocol_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Protocol ID
dimensions.description: It is a system generated unique identifier for this protocol. Protocol is a central location where all of your plans and operational instructions are linked together, serving as a starting point for your workflow in Velocity.  It consists of a collection of templates from various applications that can be copied as needed to carry out different workflows.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.protocol_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Protocol Name
dimensions.description: It is the name of the protocol

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.set_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Set ID
dimensions.description: A Set ID refers to the unique identifier for a planned planting or grow-out of material in a field or controlled environment.  Each set can consist of sub-units called entries, which may contain different materials.  The Set ID is essential for tracking and managing these plantings effectively

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.germplasm_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: A Germplasm ID is a unique identifier assigned to a specific germplasm, which is a collection of genetic resources for an organism.  This ID helps in tracking and managing genetic materials, ensuring that each germplasm can be accurately referenced in databases and inventories.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.velmat_material_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Velocity Material ID
dimensions.description: A Material ID in Velocity is a globally unique identifier for a Velocity material. This could refer to an inventory barcode, lot ID,  or catalog item ID, depending on whether it pertains to an inventory, lot, or catalog item.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.access_growergroups
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Access Grower Groups
dimensions.description: This provides the information about the growers groups associated to the record

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.access_usergroups
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Access user Groups
dimensions.description: User Groups are defined by business and consist of users from similar roles, squads, or units.  They enable visibility, sharing, and editing of trials among squad and unit members, facilitating collaboration and accountability

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.relative_maturity
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations RM
dimensions.description: Relative Maturity (RM) is a measurement in agronomy that assists farmers in determining which hybrids to use for their crops with the RM often tied to yield.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.sets_material_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Inventory ID
dimensions.description: An inventory ID is typically a unique identifier assigned to a specific inventory item within a system like MIDAS. It helps in tracking and managing inventory accurately.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.population_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Population ID
dimensions.description: a Population ID refers to a unique identifier assigned to a specific Population. This ID helps in managing and tracking the associated data of that Population

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.set_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Set Name
dimensions.description: A set name refers to the title given to a planned planting or grow out of material in a field or controlled environment.  Each set can be composed of sub-units called entries (such as plots, plants, or pots), and the set name helps to identify and manage these groupings effectively.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.line_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Line Type
dimensions.description: It is legacy piece of data that can be HYBRID, FINISHED, CODED, or SEGPOP.  This typically refers to the specific genetic lines being used in the breeding process. Different line types may have distinct genetic backgrounds and traits.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.line_code
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Line Code
dimensions.description: It is an user defined name applied to a given germplasm

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.pedigree
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Pedigree
dimensions.description: Pedigree refers to a concatenated value that includes components such as Origin, Lineage or Line Code, and Precommercial name. It is string version of parental ancestry

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.origin
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Origin
dimensions.description: The Origin in the Line Advancement Plan set entries refers to the specific source or lineage of materials, which are essential for tracking material development.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.genetic_material_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Genetic Material ID
dimensions.description: This captures midas genetic material id

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.fts_germplasmid
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations FTS Germplasm ID
dimensions.description: The Germplasm resource identifier from FTS application

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.sets_material_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Set Material Name
dimensions.description: It is material name of the set. a material name typically refers to the name associated with a specific material that used in the set. This could be linked to the Material ID, which is a globally unique identifier for a Velocity material, such as an inventory barcode, lot ID, or catalog item ID.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.catalog_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Catalog ID
dimensions.description: A Catalog ID is a unique identifier generated by the Velocity system for a specific catalog record.  It is used to describe a unique material and the attributes associated with that material, helping to tie together all the lots and inventories that represent the same material

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.catalog_seed_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Catalog Seed Type
dimensions.description: The seed type of the catalog. For example Internal Seed, Commercial Check

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.p360_product_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations p360 Product ID
dimensions.description: Describes the product 360 product identifier for velocity experiments. If the plants in the experiment are associated to a product intended to sell, this field will have values

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.source_str
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Source String
dimensions.description: The Test Set name corresponding to when the genetic material was produced.source_str from midas for a genetic material, business logic stored in text box based on linecode of parents

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.is_transgenic
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Is Trangenic
dimensions.description: Flag indicating if the germplasm contains a transgenic event

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.transgenic_events
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Transgenic Events
dimensions.description: List of transgenic events Transgenic Events represent foreign DNA from usually the same species inserted purposefully into a new speciemen through a vector

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.constructs
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Constructs
dimensions.description: This field contains the identities of the constructs used in the transformation process, provided the germplasm contains any transgenic events,

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.material_fulfillment_groups
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Material Fullfillment Groups
dimensions.description: Material fulfillment groups in the Line Advancement Plan set entries are designated user groups responsible for managing physical inventory and fulfilling material requests within the materials marketplace.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.no_of_plots_assigned
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Plots Assigned
dimensions.description: The count of entries associated with the set. Unless a set is assigned to a field or plot or entryid, this will be null

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.set_created_date
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Set Creation Date
dimensions.description: It is date of set creation. Returns a stringified date in UTC format.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.entry_number
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Entry Number
dimensions.description: The entrys order in the layout. This number is used to uniquely identify entries within a set. It is unique only within the scope of that specific set and is assigned sequentially starting from 1 up to the total number of entries in the set.  Generic entry numbers do not have any inherent business meaning or guaranteed relation to other identifiers

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.product_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Product Type
dimensions.description: It is Material category like lot, seed, inventory, catalog etc

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.entry_sequence_number
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Entry Sequence Number
dimensions.description: It is sequence order of Entry IDs in the layout .This number describes the order in which an entry should be placed in its layout. It is determined based on instructions from randomization (for trial sets) or by the nursery row pattern service (for production sets).  The sequence number indicates the placement direction and helps in constructing the layout on a map

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.set_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Set Type
dimensions.description: It is an name given to make it more readable. Example values are Simple, Trial, Production

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.population_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Population Name
dimensions.description: A population name refers to the designation given to a group of germplasm that is created during the breeding process.  Specifically, it is used to identify the progeny in the Material Marketplace, where users can see details such as the Population Name, Male Parent, and Female Parent data fields.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.material_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Material Type
dimensions.description: It is an Experiment Design name or also known as randomization Strategy Code

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.germplasm_group_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Germplasm Group ID
dimensions.description: It is a group associated to this germplasm.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.site_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Site ID
dimensions.description: Typically refers to a specific location where research, trials, or breeding activities are conducted

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.sub_site_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Sub Site ID
dimensions.description: A subsite ID refers to the unique identifier associated with a subsite within a larger site or farm structure.  Subsites are typically smaller areas that can represent different fields or rotational crops within a farm.  The system allows users to find subsites by typing in their names, which helps in retrieving the corresponding feature ID without needing to know the ID itself.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.site_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Site Name
dimensions.description: In the context of the Bayer Sites, a site name refers to the specific designation given to a Bayer Site,  which is a geometry defining an area that can be characterized in the Characterize Bayer Sites (CBS) application.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.homesite_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Homesite Name
dimensions.description: It a readable name for associated homesite

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.l0_name

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.l1_name

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.l2_name
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations County
dimensions.description: It defines the county in which the location resides. Global Geopolitical Admin Boundaries - Level 2. It is also called as District or Division

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.field_name

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.plot_id

dimensions.description: The unique identifier for a plot(typically midas_plot_id) within the Field Testing Suite (FTS).

dimensions.description: The name for the fourth level of division under the country.x
