dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Planting Session Name
dimensions.description: It is name associated with Planting Session ID

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.uom
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Sets UOM
dimensions.description: This is Sets Unit of Measure

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.area_acres
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Area Acres
dimensions.description: Area in acres

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.area_hectares
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Area Hectares
dimensions.description: Area in hectares

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.planter_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Planter Type
dimensions.description: The typical values for planter type include options such as Packet, Cassette, and Cassette (w Bottle). It refers to the specific category of planting equipment being used. When creating or editing a planting session, users can select from different planter types,  which include:  Packet: This option does not require a planter mode. Cassette: This option allows for the selection of a planter mode. Cassette (w Bottle): Similar to the Cassette option, but includes the use of bottles.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.planter_mode
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Planter Mode
dimensions.description: The Planter Mode refers to the specific settings that determine how planting sessions are configured based on the type of planter selected. When users choose a planter type, such as Cassette or Cassette (w Bottle), they will see a dropdown box for Planter Mode with various options, including Single Cell Plot (Uniform Plot Length), Single Cell Plot (Non-Uniform Plot Length), Multi Cell Plot, Strip Trial

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.instance_seq
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Instance Sequence
dimensions.description: This is a unique identifier created upon creation of a question groups in the Velocity application. Unique Identifier for question groups

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.question_code
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Question Code
dimensions.description: It is a question code created in the velocity application(https://velocity.ag/questions)

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.instanceseq_questioncode
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Instance Sequence-Question code
dimensions.description: It is concatenation of instance_seq and questioncode or MIDAS reference ID of the crop observation detail.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.answer_method
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Answer Method
dimensions.description: Method used to create answer (e.g. User Collected, System Calculated, Equipment Generated)

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.attribute
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Attribute
dimensions.description: Associated with application use and instance creation

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.uomcode
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Answers Unit of Measure Code
dimensions.description: It is a unit of measurement. For example GRAM, METER, KG, NUMBER, RATIO

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.value
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Value
dimensions.description: This is the actual answer input into the device. Value is also called as Answer or Actual Answer

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.value_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Value Type
dimensions.description: Data type for the value ('STRING', 'NUMBER', 'BOOLEAN', 'NULL', 'DATETIME', 'DATE'). Value is also called as Answer or Actual Answer

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.answer_deactivation_reason
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Answer Deactivation Reason
dimensions.description: The reason for the absolute answer deactivation

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.answer_deactivation_user
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Answer Deactivation User
dimensions.description: The user reposible  for the absolute answer deactivation

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.reason_dsr
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Reason DSR
dimensions.description: This provides the reason captured for an answer that is absolutely deactivated for DSR(Deleted Studentized Residuals) type

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.reason_qaqc
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Reason QAQC
dimensions.description: This provides the reason captured for an answer that is absolutely deactivated for QAQC(Quality Assurance Quatlity Control) type

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.is_template
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Is Template
dimensions.description: This tells is the LAP is generated using the template. True means yes it is generated using template. False means no is it not generated through use of template

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.lap_owners
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations LAP Owners
dimensions.description: In the context of the Line Advancement Application, owners are individuals responsible for the request.  The owner and the requester can be the same person, but there must be at least one owner per request.  The application allows for multiple owners by entering additional names in the Owner field or by selecting a User group in the Owner Group field.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.lap_owner_groups
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations LAP Owner Groups
dimensions.description: An owners group refers to a group of individuals who have been designated as owners of a user group.  Recording the owners group at the LAP level is important because it helps ensure that all relevant stakeholders are identified and can be held accountable for the request.  Having a clear record of ownership allows for better communication, collaboration, and tracking of responsibilities throughout the process.  Additionally, it ensures that the request is managed effectively and that all necessary parties are informed.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.pollination_parent_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Pollination Parent Type
dimensions.description: This indicates the type of parent used in the pollination process.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.progeny_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Progeny Type
dimensions.description: This indicates the type of progeny.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.created_by_user
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Created By User
dimensions.description: The Created By User in the Line Advancement Plan refers to the individual or system account that initiated the creation of a specific entry within the plan.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.created_date
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Created Date
dimensions.description: The Created Date in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the specific date when an entry was first created, providing a timeline for tracking the addition of data within the system.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.modified_by_user
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Modified By User
dimensions.description: The Modified By User in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the individual or system account responsible for the most recent changes made to an entry, ensuring accountability in data management.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.modified_date
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Modified Date
dimensions.description: The Modified Date in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the specific date when an entry was last updated or changed.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.pollination_event_status
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Pollination Event Status
dimensions.description: The pollination event status in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the current state of a pollination event, helping to track its progress from creation to completion.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.harvest_event_status
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Harvest Event Status
dimensions.description: The harvest event status in the Line Advancement Plan indicates the current state of a harvest event, helping to track its progress from initiation to completion.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.pollination_intentid
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Pollination Intent ID
dimensions.description: The pollination intent id in the Line Advancement Plan serves as a unique identifier for tracking and managing specific pollination activities associated with each entry.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.progeny
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Progeny
dimensions.description: The progeny in the Line Advancement Plan refers to the offspring generated from specific breeding activities, which are tracked and managed within the plan to assess their development and characteristics.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.male_parent
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Male Parent
dimensions.description: The male parent refers to the male entity used in breeding activities, which contributes genetic material to the offspring being tracked and managed within the plan.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.female_parent
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Female Parent
dimensions.description: The female parent refers to the female entity used in breeding activities, which provides genetic material to the offspring being tracked and managed within the plan.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.is_placeholder
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Is Placeholder
dimensions.description: This indicates whether the entry is a placeholder.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.anticipated_pollination_attempts
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Anticipated Pollination Attempts
dimensions.description: The Anticipated Pollination Attempts refers to the number of times you plan to pollinate each plant or set entry to achieve your desired harvest target quantity.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.harvest_target_quantity
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Harvest Target Quantity
dimensions.description: The harvest target quantity refers to the specific amount of plant material or flowers that you aim to collect from a breeding plan during the harvest phase.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.harvest_target_quantity_uom_uode
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Harvest Target Quantity UOM
dimensions.description: The Harvest Target Quantity UOM refers to the unit of measurement used to specify the desired amount of plant material or flowers you aim to collect during the harvest phase.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.harvest_method
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Harvest Method
dimensions.description: The Harvest Method refers to the various approaches for collecting plants during the harvest phase, which include Bulk, Select, Select & Bulk and Bulk Group.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.harvest_selections
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Harvest Selections
dimensions.description: Harvest Selections refers to the number of individual plants or entries that you plan to select for harvesting based on specific criteria.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.blocks
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Blocks
dimensions.description: Blocks are used to separate intents and create multiple sets, allowing for organized management of harvesting plans.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.block_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Block ID
dimensions.description: Block ID is a unique identifier for each block, facilitating effective management and referencing of specific blocks within the application.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.reciprocal_of_intent_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Reciprocal of Intent ID
dimensions.description: The Reciprocal of Intent ID is a unique identifier for tracking reciprocal pollination events between two plants, facilitating effective management of these intents within the application.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.male_block
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Male Block
dimensions.description: The Male Block is a designated section for organizing and managing male plant intents, ensuring effective tracking of male contributions in the breeding process.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.male_block_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Male Block ID
dimensions.description: The Male Block ID is a unique identifier for a specific block that organizes and manages male plant intents, facilitating effective tracking of male contributions in the breeding process.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.male_set_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Male Set ID
dimensions.description: The Male Set ID is a unique identifier for a specific set that organizes and manages male plant intents, essential for tracking male contributions in the breeding process.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.planting_cross_instrn_id
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Planting Cross Instruction ID
dimensions.description: Planting Cross Instruction ID is a unique identifier that outlines the guidelines for planting crosses

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.lap_cross_type
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations LAP Cross Type
dimensions.description: The LAP Cross Type refers to the specific category of cross used in breeding, including Self, Test, and Development crosses, which guide the breeding strategy and management of plant breeding activities.

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.reciprocal_cross
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Reciprocal Cross
dimensions.description: Determines if the PCI will have reciprocal crosses

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.pollination_operations
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Pollination Operations
dimensions.description: Determines pollination operation of the PCI

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.cross_type_pattern
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Cross Type Pattern
dimensions.description: Determines the cross type pattern of the PCI

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.icb
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations ICB
dimensions.description: Determines if PCI supports multiple, different male parents within a block

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.custom_row_pattern
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Custom Row Pattern
dimensions.description: Determines the gender layout of a custom pattern

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.custom_pattern_pairing
dimensions.title: Velocity Nursery Operations Custom Pattern Pairing

dimensions.name: velocity_nursery_operations.prcsg_intent_id

dimensions.description: The Keep Quantity UOM code in the Line Advancement Plan specifies the unit of measure used for quantifying the seeds or materials retained for each breeding intent.
